'''Eutonology''' is a word that [[Henri Laborit]] used for referring to his study of the state of tension or responsiveness of the organs or tissues of the body under a condition of [[Stress (biology)|stress]]. "Laboratoire d'eutonologie" was the name of Laborit's laboratory at the Boucicaut Hospital in Paris in the late 1950s.

