{{Infobox named horse | horsename = Merry Legs | image = Merry_Legs_and_Huda_Dement.jpg | caption = Merry Legs with Huda Dement | breed = [[Tennessee Walking Horse]] |discipline = [[Show horse]] | sire = Black Allan | grandsire = Allendorf | dam = Nell Dement | damsire = | foaled = 1911 | sex = Mare | color = Bay |breeder = [[Albert Dement]] | owner = | trainer = | honors= Given foundation registration F-4 }}
'''Merry Legs''' (1911-1932) was a [[Tennessee Walking Horse]] [[mare]] who was given foundation registration for her influence as a [[broodmare]]. She was also a successful [[show horse]].
==Life== Merry Legs was foaled in April 1911. She was a bay with [[sabino (horse)|sabino]] markings.<ref>http://www.westwoodfarms.net/reference/allan.html</ref> She was sired by the foundation stallion [[Black Allan (horse)|Black Allan]] F-1, out of the [[American Saddlebred]] mare Nell Dement, registration number F-3, and bred by the early breeder [[Albert Dement]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zjhWAAAAYAAJ|title=Biography of the Tennessee walking horse|publisher=}}</ref> She was a large mare at maturity, standing {{hands|15.2}} high and weighing {{convert|1200|lb}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0g1JAAAAYAAJ|title=The American Horse|publisher=}}</ref> Merry Legs was a successful show horse; as a three-year-old, she won the stake class at the [[Tennessee State Fair]]. She was also successful as a broodmare, giving birth to 13 [[foal]]s, among them the well-known Bud Allen, Last Chance, Major Allen, and Merry Boy.<ref>http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=coo.31924000436281;view=1up;seq=138;skin=mobile</ref> For her influence on the breed, she was given the foundation number F-4 when the [[TWHBEA]] was formed in 1935.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.walkerswest.com/Champs/MerryLegsF4.htm|title=Tennessee Walking horse - Merry Legs F-4 home page by Walkers West|publisher=}}</ref> She died in 1932.<ref>http://www.allbreedpedigree.com/merry+legs3</ref>
