[[File:Evolution of plants (1911) (14584806450).jpg|thumb|right|Pollen tubes, sperm, and ovule of [[Cycadophyta]]]]
'''Siphonogamy''' is a condition in plants in which [[pollen tube]]s are developed for the transfer of the male cells to the eggs. The seed plants are siphonogamous, while in the lower plants the male cells usually swim to the eggs. As a consequence, the [[spermatophyte]]s were sometimes called siphonogams.

